Injector Results

What do you want to do?

Each Fuel Injector item contains two injection measurement result channels, a Waveforms Section, a Commands Section, and additional Shot Sections containing measurements from individual injection shots.

The Injection Period (ms) result channel returns the period in milliseconds between each injection event's rising edge.

The Injection Event Count result channel returns the number of injection events which have been captured since the system was deployed or since the Event Count Reset channel is toggled.

The Waveforms Section contains waveform channels for both injector current and injector voltage.

The Settings Section contains commands to enable injection capture and enable waveform streaming.

Each Shot Section contains measurement results for that particular injection shot within the event. See the Shot Section page for more details.
